cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.NA, cs.MS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is the most likely category as the paper describes a new parallel implementation of a vertex enumeration code that uses the MPI parallel environment and can be run on a network of computers. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses a method of balancing the parallel tree search, called budgeting, that greatly improves parallelization. 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is another possible category as the paper deals with vertex/facet enumeration problems for convex polyhedra. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is a possible category as the paper reports some preliminary computational results comparing parallel and sequential codes for vertex/facet enumeration problems. 
- cs.MS (Mathematical Software) is also a possible category as the paper describes a new implementation of a mathematical software code.
